---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Screenshot from '../components/Screenshot.astro';

// Comprehensive FAQs for AI search engines and assistants
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What is the best software for managing a breeding program?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ is comprehensive breeding program management software that combines pedigree tracking with automatic COI calculation, health testing records (OFA, PennHIP, Embark), breeding cycle tracking, 8-phase breeding plan lifecycle management, client portal with e-signatures, waitlist management, invoicing and expense tracking, and an integrated marketplace. Unlike spreadsheets or basic databases, BreederHQ is purpose-built for professional breeders.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What genetics tools does BreederHQ offer?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes advanced genetics tools: multi-locus coat color, coat type, performance, temperament, eye color, and health marker tracking with a curated catalog per species, Punnett square analysis for inheritance visualization, offspring genetics simulator using Monte Carlo simulation, best match finder algorithm for optimal breeding partner suggestions with COI penalties and health risk scoring, breeding goal planner for tracking coat/health/physical trait goals, health genetics with breed-specific test profiles, and Scout AI Genetics Scanner that reads any lab PDF or photo (GenSol, Paw Print, Wisdom Panel, UC Davis, Embark) and extracts every test result with confidence scores - two clicks instead of manual entry.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ have a client portal for buyers?',
    answer: 'Yes, BreederHQ provides a comprehensive client portal where buyers get 24/7 access to: a dashboard with action items and recent activity, photo galleries of their animal, financial transparency (invoices, payments, Pay Now via Stripe integration), e-signature agreements with status tracking, direct messaging with the breeder, and categorized documents (health records, pedigree, contracts, photos).'
  },
  {
    question: 'What species does BreederHQ support?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ supports professional breeders of dogs, cats, horses, goats, alpacas, llamas, rabbits, sheep, and cattle with species-specific tools for each. This includes species-specific breeding cycle timelines, health testing protocols, genetics tracking, and marketplace visibility appropriate for each species.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does BreederHQ track breeding cycles?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ offers comprehensive breeding cycle tracking with species-specific timelines. Features include heat cycle tracking with Full vs Likely windows for conservative planning, hormone testing window calculations, progesterone tracking, breeding plans with 8-phase lifecycle (Planning, Committed, Bred, Birthed, Weaned, Placement Started, Placement Completed, Complete), Gantt chart timeline views, and breeding calendar with scheduling.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What business tools does BreederHQ include?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes complete business management: invoicing with line items (deposits, fees, goods, discounts, tax), payment recording (Cash, Check, Credit Card, ACH, PayPal, Venmo, Zelle), expense tracking across 12 categories (Vet, Supplies, Food, Grooming, Breeding, Facility, Marketing, Labor, Insurance, Registration, Travel), financial dashboard with MTD metrics, breeding plan financial rollups with revenue analysis, and CSV export.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does BreederHQ help with waitlist management?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ provides comprehensive waitlist management: buyer applications and intake forms, waitlist position tracking with automated notifications, family-to-animal matching tools, deposit tracking tied to waitlist positions, client portal access for buyers to see their position and receive updates, and communication templates for efficient buyer communication.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does identity and credential display work on BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ does not verify or vouch for breeders. What appears on a profile comes from three layers: identity confirmation via Stripe Identity (operated by Stripe, Inc.), public-registry passthrough where issuing bodies maintain a public registry (OFA, AKC, AFA, etc.) with a link to the source record, and the breeder\u2019s own attestation for everything else. BreederHQ may also display Profile Indicators based on platform account history (response time, completed transactions). See /trust for the full policy.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the best alternative to spreadsheets for breeders?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ is the best alternative to spreadsheets for professional breeders. Unlike spreadsheets which scatter data across multiple files with no connections, BreederHQ centralizes everything: pedigrees link to health records, breeding plans connect to waitlists, invoices tie to animals, and all data flows to your marketplace listing. Plus you get automation, reminders, client portals, and genetics tools that spreadsheets cannot provide.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ have a marketplace for selling animals?',
    answer: 'Yes, BreederHQ includes an integrated marketplace where your breeding program data automatically powers your listings. Features include breeder profiles with discovery filters (species, breed, location), identity and credential indicators on profiles (Stripe Identity passthrough, public-registry passthrough where supported), animal program listings (Stud Services, Guardian, Trained, Rehome, Co-Ownership), offspring group (litter) listings, individual animal listings, and a buyer dashboard with saved listings, inquiries, and waitlist positions.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can BreederHQ track show titles and competition results?',
    answer: 'Yes, BreederHQ includes a titles and achievements system supporting Conformation, Obedience, Agility, Field, Herding, Tracking, Rally, Producing, and Performance categories. Track competition results for Shows, Trials, Races, and Tests with status tracking (In Progress, Earned, Verified), points/major wins, document verification, and producing records showing offspring counts and champion tracking.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What pedigree features does BreederHQ offer?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ offers comprehensive pedigree management: multi-generation pedigree visualization with configurable depth, automatic COI (coefficient of inbreeding) calculation with risk levels (LOW, MODERATE, HIGH, CRITICAL), common ancestor tracking with contribution percentages, cross-tenant network animal linking via Global Animal ID (GAID) or Exchange Code, and ReactFlow interactive tree visualization. Pedigrees connect to health records and marketplace listings.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does BreederHQ compare to GoodDog or PuppyFind?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ is fundamentally different: instead of just listing animals, breeders manage their entire breeding program on the platform. This creates unprecedented transparency, because buyers see actual health testing documentation, pedigrees with COI calculation, breeding history, and program practices from the breeder\u2019s real program records. It is not just a listing site; it is breeding program management software with an integrated marketplace.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ track vaccinations, medications, and health records?',
    answer: 'Yes, BreederHQ includes comprehensive health tracking: vaccination records with species-specific protocols and expiration alerts, medication tracking with treatment courses, individual dose logging, and withdrawal period countdowns for competition compliance, health testing record management (OFA, PennHIP, genetic panels), Scout AI-powered document upload that auto-extracts medication details from vet invoices, health report PDF export with secure sharing, and visibility controls for what buyers can see through the client portal or marketplace.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What communication tools does BreederHQ provide?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes powerful communication tools: Communications Hub (unified inbox) combining email and direct messages, email and message templates with variable insertion (contact name, animal name, etc.), document bundles for quick email attachment, business hours configuration with Quick Responder badge tracking, and rule-based auto-replies on Pro and Enterprise plans (instant acknowledgments, away messages, keyword-triggered responses, and business-hours scheduling).'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ have nutrition and feeding tracking?',
    answer: 'Yes. BreederHQ includes comprehensive nutrition tracking: a food product catalog with automatic cost-per-ounce calculation, per-animal feeding plans with portion and schedule configuration, feeding logs with appetite scoring (1-5 scale) to catch health issues early, food transition documentation with outcome tracking, and cost analytics showing spending trends across your entire program. Feeding plans can be shared with buyers through the client portal.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can BreederHQ watermark my photos and documents?',
    answer: 'Yes, for the documents you share with buyers. BreederHQ can watermark contracts, health records, and other PDFs or images with text or your logo, and you control position, opacity, and size. Watermarking is opt-in per document, so you choose which files carry it, and watermarks are applied when buyers view or download a file through the client portal while you always keep clean originals. Every view and download is recorded in a complete audit trail, so you know who accessed your content. Automatic watermarking of public marketplace and profile photos is on our roadmap and not yet active.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ warn about dangerous breeding combinations?',
    answer: 'Yes. BreederHQ automatically detects lethal gene combinations and warns you before you breed. This includes Double Merle detection in dogs (which can cause deafness and blindness), Lethal White Overo in horses (always fatal), HYPP, HERDA, GBED, and other species-specific lethal combinations. The system checks both parents genetic test results when you plan a breeding and displays a red warning banner if a dangerous pairing is detected.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What rearing protocols does BreederHQ support?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes comprehensive rearing protocol tracking: Early Neurological Stimulation (ENS) with day-by-day tracking from days 3-16, Early Scent Introduction (ESI) with 16 built-in scent options, Rule of 7s socialization checklist, Puppy Culture exercises, and Avidog protocols. You can also create custom protocols with the Protocol Builder. Per-puppy progress tracking, batch completion for efficiency, community sharing of proven protocols, and completion certificates for buyers are all included.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ include temperament testing?',
    answer: 'Yes. BreederHQ includes two standardized assessments: the Volhard Puppy Aptitude Test (PAT) with all 10 subtests for general temperament evaluation, and the Gun Dog Aptitude Test with 10 field-specific tests for sporting dog breeders. Volhard results also include Working-Dog Role Suitability analysis that evaluates puppies for six roles: K9/Protection, Military Working Dog, Guide Dog, Therapy Dog, Search & Rescue, and Detection. Scores are calculated automatically with radar charts, temperament classification, and placement recommendations. Results can be shared with buyers through the portal.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does BreederHQ help prevent fading puppy syndrome?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ includes comprehensive neonatal care tracking designed to catch problems early: weight tracking with sparkline visualizations showing trends at a glance, batch weight entry for quick logging, automatic weight anomaly alerts (no gain in 24 hours, weight loss, below litter average), care log timelines documenting interventions (tube feeding, supplementing, warming), veterinary intervention tracking, and a neonatal dashboard with status indicators (Thriving, Monitor, Attention Needed). These features help breeders identify struggling puppies before its too late.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ support contracts and e-signatures?',
    answer: 'Yes. BreederHQ includes professional contract management: contract templates with auto-fill for animal name, buyer info, and price; multiple contract types (pet, breeding rights, co-ownership, stud service, guardian); digital e-signatures allowing clients to sign from any device; signature audit trail with timestamps; automatic sending when deposit is received; document bundles combining contracts with health guarantees and care guides; and permanent storage in the client portal. No need for separate DocuSign or HelloSign subscriptions.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ have an AI assistant for breeders?',
    answer: 'Yes. BreederHQ includes Scout AI, a data-aware assistant that connects directly to your breeding data. Ask natural-language questions about your animals, breeding plans, finances, contacts, waitlists, offspring, and medications-and get instant answers without searching through records. Scout uses 13 specialized tools to search your data, and can export results as CSV, generate printable reports, and create PIN-protected health report PDFs to share with your vet. Conversations are saved across sessions. A separate Help Assistant provides contextual guidance, interactive feature tours, and a searchable help center.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ have a mobile app?',
    answer: 'Yes. The BreederHQ Mobile Companion is a native iOS and Android app that pairs with the BreederHQ web platform. It is intentionally not a full replacement for the web app — it is a focused, on-the-go companion for the moments breeding actually happens (the barn, the vet office, the show ring, the birthing area at 2 AM). Use it to record weights, log a vet visit, snap an expense receipt, pull up a pedigree, reply to a buyer message, or mark a task done. The deeper work — building breeding plans, managing your storefront, configuring contracts, running reports, genetics analysis — stays in the web app. Everything syncs instantly between the two.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="BreederHQ - Professional Breeding Management Software"
  description="Breeding management software for breeders of dogs, cats, horses, goats, alpacas, llamas, rabbits, sheep, and cattle. Pedigrees, genetics, health testing, waitlists, and more."
  faqs={faqs}
  hideLogo={true}
>

  <main>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- HERO: Ecosystem Positioning                  -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-stone-50 to-white pt-8 pb-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <img src="/logo.png" alt="BreederHQ" class="h-40 w-auto mx-auto mb-8" />

          <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-6xl leading-tight">
            Smart Tools for Smart Breeders.<br />
            <span class="text-primary">A Trusted Marketplace for Everyone.</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
            BreederHQ is the platform where professional breeders run their operations,
            buyers discover verified programs backed by real data,
            and service providers reach an active community of animal professionals.
          </p>

          <!-- Three-audience CTA row -->
          <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a
              href="/for-breeders"
              class="relative overflow-hidden bg-primary text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold w-full sm:w-72 text-center shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl hover:scale-105 transition-all duration-300"
            >
              <span class="relative z-10">I'm a Breeder</span>
              <span class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(110deg,transparent_25%,rgba(255,255,255,0.2)_50%,transparent_75%)] animate-[shimmer_3s_ease-in-out_infinite] bg-[length:200%_100%]"></span>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://marketplace.breederhq.com"
              class="relative overflow-hidden bg-stone-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold w-full sm:w-72 text-center shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl hover:scale-105 hover:bg-stone-600 transition-all duration-300"
            >
              <span class="relative z-10">Browse the Marketplace</span>
              <span class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(110deg,transparent_25%,rgba(255,255,255,0.15)_50%,transparent_75%)] animate-[shimmer_3.5s_ease-in-out_infinite] bg-[length:200%_100%]"></span>
            </a>
            <a
              href="/for-providers"
              class="relative overflow-hidden bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold w-full sm:w-72 text-center shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl hover:scale-105 hover:bg-emerald-600 transition-all duration-300"
            >
              <span class="relative z-10">I'm a Service Provider</span>
              <span class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(110deg,transparent_25%,rgba(255,255,255,0.15)_50%,transparent_75%)] animate-[shimmer_4s_ease-in-out_infinite] bg-[length:200%_100%]"></span>
            </a>
          </div>

          <style>
            @keyframes shimmer {
              0% { background-position: 200% 0; }
              100% { background-position: -200% 0; }
            }
          </style>

          <!-- Breed club admin secondary entry -->
          <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
            Breed club administrator?
            <a href="/for-breed-clubs" class="text-primary font-medium hover:underline">See BreederHQ for Breed Clubs &rarr;</a>
          </p>

          <!-- Hero screenshot: real platform dashboard -->
          <div class="mt-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
            <Screenshot
              id="platform-dashboard"
              alt="BreederHQ platform dashboard showing breeding pipeline, litters in care, waitlist, and finances"
              loading="eager"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SUB-HERO FEATURE STRIP (SEO crawl prominence) -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="bg-white py-8 border-t border-stone-100">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">

          <a
            href="/workflows/heat-tracking"
            class="group block p-5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white hover:border-amber-400 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <span class="inline-flex w-9 h-9 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-lg" aria-hidden="true">🔄</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Heat Cycle Tracking</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Track heats, ovulation timing, and breeding windows by species.</p>
            <span class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-medium" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>

          <a
            href="/compare/best-dog-breeding-software"
            class="group block p-5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white hover:border-amber-400 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <span class="inline-flex w-9 h-9 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-lg" aria-hidden="true">🐕</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Dog Breeding Software</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Compare the eight dog breeding software tools real breeders shortlist in 2026.</p>
            <span class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-medium" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>

          <a
            href="/tools/breeding-planner"
            class="group block p-5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white hover:border-amber-400 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <span class="inline-flex w-9 h-9 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-lg" aria-hidden="true">📅</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Free Breeding Planner</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Calculate gestation timelines and milestone dates. No signup.</p>
            <span class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-medium" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>

          <a
            href="/tools"
            class="group block p-5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white hover:border-amber-400 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <span class="inline-flex w-9 h-9 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-lg" aria-hidden="true">🧰</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Free Tools</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Free utilities for breeders. Standalone or with the platform.</p>
            <span class="text-amber-600 text-sm font-medium" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
          </a>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- HOW IT CONNECTS: Simple 3-step flow          -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white border-t border-stone-100">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Software. Marketplace. Community.<br />All Connected.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Most platforms make you choose: manage your program <em>or</em> get discovered.
            BreederHQ does both, and the data flows between them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Three connected steps -->
        <div class="space-y-0">

          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-center">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex justify-center">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center text-lg font-bold">1</div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-5">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Breeders run their programs here</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Health records, genetics, breeding plans, waitlists, invoicing, client portals -
                the entire operation lives on BreederHQ. No spreadsheets, no scattered tools.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-6 bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center text-sm">
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl mb-1">🧬</div>
                  <div class="text-gray-600">Genetics</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl mb-1">📋</div>
                  <div class="text-gray-600">Breeding Plans</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl mb-1">💰</div>
                  <div class="text-gray-600">Invoicing</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl mb-1">❤️</div>
                  <div class="text-gray-600">Health Records</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl mb-1">📬</div>
                  <div class="text-gray-600">Client Portal</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-2xl mb-1">📊</div>
                  <div class="text-gray-600">Waitlists</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Connector arrow -->
          <div class="flex justify-center py-4 md:pl-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-stone-300">
              <div class="w-px h-8 bg-stone-300"></div>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 font-medium mt-1">That data becomes</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-center">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex justify-center">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-stone-800 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-lg font-bold">2</div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-5">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Buyers find verified programs</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Because breeders manage their real data here, marketplace listings are backed by actual
                health testing, documented pedigrees, and breeding history, not self-reported claims.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-6">
              <Screenshot
                id="marketplace-breeder-profile"
                alt="A real breeder profile in BreederHQ Marketplace showing health practices, registry affiliations, and breeding philosophy"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Connector arrow -->
          <div class="flex justify-center py-4 md:pl-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-stone-300">
              <div class="w-px h-8 bg-stone-300"></div>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-xs text-stone-400 font-medium mt-1">And the community grows</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-center">
            <div class="md:col-span-1 flex justify-center">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-emerald-700 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-lg font-bold">3</div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-5">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Service providers get discovered</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Vets, trainers, photographers, and transporters: one listing puts your services
                in front of breeders, buyers, and pet owners searching for animal services.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-6 bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center text-base">🩺</div>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">Veterinary</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center text-base">🎓</div>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">Training</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center text-base">📸</div>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">Photography</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center text-base">🚐</div>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">Transport</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center text-base">✂️</div>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">Grooming</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center text-base">🏠</div>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">Boarding</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- THREE AUDIENCE DEEP-DIVES                    -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-stone-50">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Built for Three Audiences. Designed as One.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

          <!-- FOR BREEDERS -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-stone-200 overflow-hidden shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
